<h1>Weather Models</h1>

<div class="well">
  <i class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></i> A weather model updates the weather
  for your simluation, providing needed sunlight, precipitation, and 
  temperature.  Weather models typically draw from historical weather
  data, mathematical models of weather performance, or is randomly 
  generated.  Read the model descriptions to learn how a specific weather
  model works.
</div>

<div class="row">
  <% @weather.each do |weather| %>
    <%= render weather %>
  <% end %>
</div>

<%= link_to 'New Weather Model', new_weather_path %>
